59年","1215":"1215年","1224":"1224年","1179":"1179年","ABT 1179":"大约1179年","1180":"1180年","Harley, Shropshire, England":"英国史洛普爾哈爾","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"英国史洛普爾","lifeSummary":"Robert Randulph于大约1179年出生在英国史洛普爾。他和Mrs Robert Randulph至少有1个女儿。"},"hr":{"ABT 1179–":"oko 1179.–preminuo","1180–Female":"1180–preminula","1204–1224":"1204.–1224","1179–Male":"1179–preminuo","1204":"1204.","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"oko 1179.","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England"},"cs":{"ABT 1179–":"okolo 1179–Zesnulý","1180–Female":"1180–Zesnulá","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Zesnulý","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"okolo 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, Anglie","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, Anglie"},"da":{"ABT 1179–":"omkring 1179–Afdød","1180–Female":"1180–Afdød","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Afdød","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"omkring 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England"},"nl":{"ABT 1179–":"circa 1179–Overleden","1180–Female":"1180–Overleden","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Overleden","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"circa 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England"},"en":{"ABT 1179–":"about 1179–Deceased","1180–Female":"1180–Deceased","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Deceased","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"about 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Randulph","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and German: from <i>Randolf</i>, an ancient Germanic personal name composed of the elements <i>rand</i> ‘rim (of a shield), shield’ + <i>wolf</i> ‘wolf’. This was introduced into England by the Normans in Old French forms of two different ancient Germanic personal names which became confused with each other: <i>Randulf</i> (from <i>rand</i> ‘(shield-)edge’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’) and <i>Rannulf</i> (from <i>hraf(a)n</i> ‘raven’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’).","History: An American family bearing this surname are descended from William Randolph (<i>c.</i> 1651–1711), a planter and merchant, a member of a family that originally came from Sussex, England. William Randolph emigrated from Warwickshire to VA <i>c.</i> 1673. He was a forebear of Thomas Jefferson and Robert E. Lee. Randolph had seven sons, each of whom inherited an estate, the name of which was sometimes added to their own, such as Sir John Randolph of Tazewell. His great-grandsons included Edmund Randolph (1753–1813), first attorney general of the US and one of the framers of the US Constitution, and the diplomat and statesman John Randolph of Roanoke (1773–1833), who served as US minister to Russia."],"variants":[{"name":"Rand","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Rand</i>, a pet form of <i>Randolf</i>. Compare   Randolph  ,   Randall  ,   Randy  , and see also   Rance  .","English: habitational name from Rand (Lincolnshire), Rand Grange (North Yorkshire), or Raunds (Northamptonshire), all of which derive from Old English <i>rand</i> ‘edge, border, rim’.","German: from a short form of any of various ancient Germanic compound personal names formed with <i>rand</i> ‘rim (of a shield)’. Compare 1 above."]},{"name":"Randerson","meanings":["English (West and East Yorkshire): patronymic from the Middle English personal name <i>Randolf</i> (see   Randolph  ) + <i>-son</i>. In East Anglia the name may also have been influenced by a form of the now rare or extinct <b>Rendlesham</b>, itself from the place of that name in Suffolk. The placename probably derives from an Old English personal name <i>Rendel</i> (genitive <i>Rendeles</i>) + Old English <i>hām</i> ‘village, homestead’."]},{"name":"Randolf","meanings":["English and German: variant of   Randolph  ."]},{"name":"Randall","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): common colloquial pronunciation of   Randolph  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":36,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":45,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":80,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Randulph was born about 1179, in Shropshire, England. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs Robert Randulph."},"et":{"ABT 1179–":"umbes 1179–Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Surnud","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"umbes 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England"},"fi":{"ABT 1179–":"noin 1179–Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"noin 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, England","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, England"},"fr":{"ABT 1179–":"environ 1179–Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","1204–1224":"1204–1224","1179–Male":"1179–Décédé","1204":"1204","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","ABT 1179":"environ 1179","1180":"1180","Harley, Shropshire, England":"Harley, Shropshire, Angleterre","Of Westhay,Shropshire,England":"Shropshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Robert Randulph est né environ 1179, à Shropshire, Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Mrs Robert Randulph."},"de":{"ABT 1